<br>
Since you went with the completely silly looking, skirt wearing barbarian... I'll assume looks don't mean that much? /tease <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   If thats the case, items with +str, dex and agi will be of most use to you early on.  Ac, hp and sta are important too...  but as an evading rogue, you won't be getting hit much until higher level raids come into the picture with those nasty AE'in mobs.  My advice to ya is to check out the bazaar and look up those stats.  <br>
<br>
Few good items to check out off the top of my head:<br>
-Barbed ringmail (I think its 30 ac 9 str 50 hp) about 3.5-5k<br>
-Crystal Chitin Gaunts (20 ac 10 str... and umm..others) <br>
-Silver Chitin Wristband (ac 15 str/dex 7 40hp)<br>
-Shimmering Terror Hide Cloak (decent stats, but adds 50hp)<br>
-Hardened Bone Spear (12/25  +15 str)<br>
-Crown of the Hive (AC/agi/dex +10 FR/CR +15)<br>
       ...and if you do want a slick rogue black look, black ice legs and arms might be worth checking out.. the ac is so-so, and they add str.<br>
<br>
That crown is droppable (I know, I wear it myself)... but it may be hard to find.  Anyhoo..just a few suggestions.  The weapons you have are good, I just suggested the other as a higher damage piercer because you will notice that makes a HUGE difference in backstabs.  Some rogues argue that having a faster weapon is best, but in my personal opinion, the 25 delay over 20 delay is well worth it, particularly if you'll have a haste item.  I also highly recommend having a nice 1HS to use in your offhand... it is wonderful to have the skill maxed, and it would suck to miss out on a great weapon in the future if you didn't have the skill.<br>
<br>
One final little note about phase spider carapace, I'm assuming if you are thinking about buying one you might already have a decent price... but whenever I've been in the bazaar shopping, I've noticed them selling for outrageous amounts that would break your bank if you just have that 15-20k to spend (not sure that would even buy one).  It is a great item with more stats than the barbed ringmail... but then the ringmail has slightly higher ac, str AND hp. Your call of course... I just think the barbed ringmail is nearly as good, wonderful really for the money you'd save... but I'm a frugal shopper <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
